In order to push this plugin to it's subversion repository, there's a couple commands
we will use quite often

# Sync the subtree with the remote branch

`git merge --squash -s subtree --no-commit click_php/master`

Merge our local branch with the remote subtree

# Pushing commits to the SVN repository

`git svn rebase`

Sync the current branch with any commits on subversion.

`git svn dcommit`

Loop through all the GIT commits and add SVN copies

# Tag a new subversion release

`git tag -a $1 -m "tagging $1"`

Create the new tag in GIT

`git svn tag "$1"`

Create a new subversion tag